    "body": "Recent profile shows that the node spends 15% of CPU time in the main thread doing discv5 work. This is excessive. Please @wemeetagain take a look when you can focusing on\r\n- Are our network parameters similar to other clients? Are we handling more messages than necessary?\r\n- Is there any redundant crypto opts we could optimize? Is is really necessary to create peerIds at that point? Maybe we can defer to when the app layer decides to connect to that peer.",
